properties.areaDesc: Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 4 at 12:09PM MST until February 5 at 1:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG GUSTY WINDS WILL RETURN TO THE SOUTHWEST PLATTE COUNTY
LATE TONIGHT ALONG WITH PERIODS OF BLOWING SNOW...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect from 2 AM to 1 PM MST Wednesday.

* WHAT...West to southwest winds will increase late tonight with
sustained winds of 35 to 45 mph and gusts up to 65 mph expected
towards sunrise.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and southwest Platte County,
including Bordeaux.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous,
especially for lightweight, high profile vehicles including
camping and tractor trailers. Blowing snow will result in
visibility below 1 mile at times and slick roads.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO 1 PM MST WEDNESDAY
